ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This course is an easy, entry-level yet informative course on Database. I would recommend it to anyone who hasn't had a deep understanding of database. Because this course really helps to familiarize one with database.
Yes. It's a good fundamental CS course.
I will strongly recommend others to take it. Good class. Educative.
It is a good course. You can learn what you want in a introductive DB course.
Yes. If you want to learn basic database concepts, choose it.
If you want to know the practicality of DBMS take this course. Do not expect to know the implementation of DBMS in detail or how to create web databases or applications that use databases.
I would recommend this course to any student who wants an introduction to the subject. It was quite comprehensive and introduced a variety of different topics.
If you have learned database before you may find a lot of knowledge covered you may learned before. However, I remember you to take this, because you can always learn something more deatail.
I would strongly recommend the course to anyone who would like to get into databases.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Database is a ubiquitous application. It is very likely that database will play a role in my future research and/or career.
Database is an important branch of CS. What I have been taught is very helpful.
Great course on databases. Gives a clear concise overview.
I thought it provided a good introduction to databases and is a useful course to take.
This course is vey helpful for my interview.
it helps me prepare the database knowledge which is necessary for job search and future career development
